{"title_page": "Just a Touch of Love (song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Just a Touch of Love\n| cover      = Just_a_Touch_of_Love.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[C+C Music Factory]]\n| album      = [[Gonna Make You Sweat]]\n| released   = August 15, 1991\n| format     =\n| recorded   = 1990\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Dance-pop]]\n| length     = 5:38\n| label      =\n| writer     = [[Robert Clivill\u00e9s]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = [[Things That Make You Go Hmmm...]]\n| prev_year  = 1991\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|X-F2ick5RQU|\"Just a Touch of Love\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Just a Touch of Love'''\"  is a 1991 single written by [[Robert Clivill\u00e9s]] and performed by [[C+C Music Factory]].  The single also known as \"Just a Touch of Love (Everyday)\", which featured vocals by [[Zelma Davis]], was the duo's fourth release from their album, ''[[Gonna Make You Sweat]]''.  \"Just a Touch of Love\" was the duo's fourth number one on the US dance charts.<ref>{{cite book |title= Hot Dance/Disco: 1974-2003|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=49}}</ref>  On other US charts, the single went to #50 on the [[Hot 100]] and #83 on the soul singles chart.<ref>{{cite book |title= Top R&B/Hip-Hop Singles: 1942-2004|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=100}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n''[[Music & Media]]'' commented, \"More dance from American groove masters C&C. Just a touch of rap and a little bit of scratching are covered in soulful and meaty vocals. Slightly reminiscent of the '70s, there are echoes of [[Chic (band)|Chic]], among others.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/90s/1991/MM-1991-11-30.pdf|title=Previews: Singles|publisher=Music & Media|date=30 November 1991|page=11|accessdate=19 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Chart (1991)\n! Peak<br/>position\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]\n|align=\"center\"|50\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot Dance Club Songs|Hot Dance Club Play]]<ref>{{cite book |title= Hot Dance/Disco: 1974-2003|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=49}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Singles]]<ref>{{cite book |title= Top R&B/Hip-Hop Singles: 1942-2004|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=100}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|83\n|-\n|Australia (ARIA Charts)]\n|align=\"center\"|27\n|}\n\n==Song in popular culture==\n*\"Just a Touch of Love\" was featured in the 1992 film, ''[[Sister Act]]'', and in the second season of the 2018 television series [[Pose (TV series)|Pose]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of number-one dance singles of 1992 (U.S.)]]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n[[Category:1991 singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Robert Clivill\u00e9s]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:1991 songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Just a Touch of Love\n| cover      = Just_a_Touch_of_Love.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[C+C Music Factory]]\n| album      = [[Gonna Make You Sweat]]\n| released   = August 15, 1991\n| format     =\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Dance-pop]]\n| length     = 5:38\n| label      =\n| writer     = [[Robert Clivill\u00e9s]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = [[Things That Make You Go Hmmm...]]\n| prev_year  = 1991\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|X-F2ick5RQU|\"Just a Touch of Love\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Just a Touch of Love'''\"  is a 1991 single written by [[Robert Clivill\u00e9s]] and performed by [[C+C Music Factory]].  The single also known as \"Just a Touch of Love (Everyday)\", which featured vocals by [[Zelma Davis]], was the duo's fourth release from their album, ''[[Gonna Make You Sweat]]''.  \"Just a Touch of Love\" was the duo's fourth number one on the US dance charts.<ref>{{cite book |title= Hot Dance/Disco: 1974-2003|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=49}}</ref>  On other US charts, the single went to #50 on the [[Hot 100]] and #83 on the soul singles chart.<ref>{{cite book |title= Top R&B/Hip-Hop Singles: 1942-2004|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=100}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n''[[Music & Media]]'' commented, \"More dance from American groove masters C&C. Just a touch of rap and a little bit of scratching are covered in soulful and meaty vocals. Slightly reminiscent of the '70s, there are echoes of [[Chic (band)|Chic]], among others.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/90s/1991/MM-1991-11-30.pdf|title=Previews: Singles|publisher=Music & Media|date=30 November 1991|page=11|accessdate=19 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Chart (1991)\n! Peak<br/>position\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]\n|align=\"center\"|50\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot Dance Club Songs|Hot Dance Club Play]]<ref>{{cite book |title= Hot Dance/Disco: 1974-2003|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=49}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Singles]]<ref>{{cite book |title= Top R&B/Hip-Hop Singles: 1942-2004|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=100}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|83\n|-\n|Australia (ARIA Charts)]\n|align=\"center\"|27\n|}\n\n==Song in popular culture==\n*\"Just a Touch of Love\" was featured in the 1992 film, ''[[Sister Act]]'', and in the second season of the 2018 television series [[Pose (TV series)|Pose]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of number-one dance singles of 1992 (U.S.)]]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n[[Category:1991 singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Robert Clivill\u00e9s]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:1991 songs]]\n", "name_user": "2603:6000:8d00:92aa:d900:772d:2d5a:6575", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Just_a_Touch_of_Love_(song)"}
{"title_page": "The Fourteen Infallibles", "text_new": "{{The Fourteen Infallible}}\n{{Shia Islam}}\n'''The Fourteen Infallibles''' ({{lang-ar|\u0671\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0635\u064f\u0648\u0645\u064f\u0648\u0646 \u0671\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0631\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0629 \u0639\u064e\u0634\u064e\u0631}}, ''{{transl|ar|DIN|al-Ma\u02bf\u1e63\u016bm\u016bn al-\u02beArba\u02bfah \u02bfA\u0161ar}}''; {{lang-fa|\u0686\u0647\u0627\u0631\u062f\u0647 \u0645\u0639\u0635\u0648\u0645}}, ''{{transl|fa|DIN|\u010cah\u00e2rdah Ma's\u016bm}}'') in [[Twelver|Twelver Shia Islam]] are the Islamic prophet [[Muhammad]], his daughter [[Fatima Zahra]], and [[Twelve Imams|the Twelve Imams]]. All are considered to be [[ismah|infallible]] under the theological concept of [[Ismah]].<ref>{{Harvnb|Dabashi|2006|p=463}}</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Corbin|1993|p=48}}</ref> Accordingly, they have the power to commit sin but by their nature are able to avoid doing so, which is regarded as a miraculous gift from [[God in Islam|God]].<ref>{{harvnb|Nasr|Dabashi|Nasr|1989|p=98}}</ref> The Infallibles are believed to follow only God's desire in their actions because of their supreme righteousness, consciousness, and love for God.<ref>{{harvnb|Donaldson|1933|p=326}}</ref> They are also regarded as being immune to error in practical matters, in calling people to religion, and in the perception of divine knowledge.<ref>{{harvnb|Ansariyan|2007|p=89}}</ref> [[Shia]]s believe the Fourteen Infallibles are superior to the rest of creation and to the other major [[Prophets in Islam|prophets]].<ref name=\"harvnb|Algar|1990\">{{harvnb|Algar|1990}}</ref>\n\n== Family tree ==\n[[File:Names of imameen.jpg|thumb|right|Calligraphic depiction of fourteen infallibles names.]]\n{{Familytree/start}}\n{{Familytree|boxstyle=background: #DDFFDD| | |MHMAD| | | | |MHMAD=[[Muhammad]]<br/>({{lang|ar|\u0645\u064f\u062d\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0651\u062f}})}}\n{{Familytree|boxstyle=background: #DDFFDD| | | |!| | | | ||