/english/library/pro_ahl/imam09_jawad/the_life_of_imam_jawad/index.htm |year=2005 |publisher=Ansariyan Publications |isbn=978-964-438-653-4 |ref=harv |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713121545/http://www.maaref-foundation.com/english/library/pro_ahl/imam09_jawad/the_life_of_imam_jawad/index.htm |archivedate=July 13, 2014 }}\n* {{cite book|last=Rayshahri|first=M. Muhammadi|title=The scale of wisdom: a compendium of Shi'a Hadith|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pfcCps0I8MUC&pg=PA68|date=12 January 2008|publisher=ICAS Press|isbn=978-1-904063-34-6|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last= Rizvi|first=Sayyid Saeed Akhtar|title=Imamate: The vicegerency of the Holy Prophet|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0f2qAgAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PP2#v=onepage&q&f=false|year=1988|publisher=Bilal Muslim Mission of Tanzania|isbn=978-9976-956-13-9}}\n* {{cite book | last=Sachedina | first=Abdulaziz Abdulhussein | authorlink=Abdulaziz Sachedina | title= The Just Ruler (al-sult\u0101n Al-\u02bb\u0101dil) in Sh\u012b\u02bbite Islam: The Comprehensive Authority of the Jurist in Imamite Jurisprudence| publisher=Oxford University Press | year=1988 | isbn=0-19-511915-0|ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book|last = Tabatabaei|first = Sayyid Mohammad Hosayn|title = Shi'ite Islam|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Be5DeNM8d1EC&pg=PA258|year = 1975|isbn =978-0-87395-390-0 |ref = harv| others=Translated by [[Seyyed Hossein Nasr|Sayyid Hossein Nasr]]|publisher=SUNY Press}}\n* {{cite book | last=Tabatabaei | first=Sayyid Mohammad Hosayn | others= Translated by [[Seyyed Hossein Nasr]] | authorlink=Allameh Tabatabaei | title= Shi'ite Islam| publisher=SUNY press| year=1979 | isbn=978-0-87395-272-9|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last= Walbridge|first=Linda S.|title=The Most Learned of the Shi`a: The Institution of the Marja` Taqlid|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_FVf4V4aXWgC&pg=PA103|date=6 August 2001|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-534393-9}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061206200206/http://www.al-islam.org/masoom/bios/table.html A Chronological List of the Fourteen Infallibles]\n* [http://www.wofis.com/asset/Books/001.pdf A Brief History of the Fourteen Infallibles] by WOFIS World Organization for Islamic Services Tehran -Iran\n* [http://www.alimamali.com/html/eng/books/mokhtasar/ The Brief History of the Fourteen Infallibles] by Mohammad Hussein il\u2019adeeb\n\n{{Religious family trees}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fourteen Infallible, The}}\n[[Category:Shia Islam]]\n[[Category:Shia belief and doctrine]]\n[[Category:Twelvers]]\n[[Category:Shia theology]]\n[[Category:Islam-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists of Muslims]]\n[[Category:Muslim family trees]]\n[[Category:Islamic terminology]]\n[[Category:The Fourteen Infallibles| ]]\n[[Category:Family of Muhammad]]\n[[Category:Banu Hashim]]\n", "text_old": "{{The Fourteen Infallible}}\n{{Shia Islam}}\n'''The Fourteen Infallibles''' ({{lang-ar|\u0671\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0635\u064f\u0648\u0645\u064f\u0648\u0646 \u0671\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0631\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0629 \u0639\u064e\u0634\u064e\u0631}}, ''{{transl|ar|DIN|al-Ma\u02bf\u1e63\u016bm\u016bn al-\u02beArba\u02bfah \u02bfA\u0161ar}}''; {{lang-fa|\u0686\u0647\u0627\u0631\u062f\u0647 \u0645\u0639\u0635\u0648\u0645}}, ''{{transl|fa|DIN|\u010cah\u00e2rdah Ma's\u016bm}}'') in [[Twelver|Twelver Shia Islam]] are the Islamic prophet [[Muhammad]], his daughter [[Fatima Zahra]], and [[Twelve Imams|the Twelve Imams]]. All are considered to be [[ismah|infallible]] under the theological concept of [[Ismah]].<ref>{{Harvnb|Dabashi|2006|p=463}}</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Corbin|1993|p=48}}</ref> Accordingly, they have the power to commit sin but by their nature are able to avoid doing so, which is regarded as a miraculous gift from [[God in Islam|God]].<ref>{{harvnb|Nasr|Dabashi|Nasr|1989|p=98}}</ref> The Infallibles are believed to follow only God's desire in their actions because of their supreme righteousness, consciousness, and love for God.<ref>{{harvnb|Donaldson|1933|p=326}}</ref> They are also regarded as being immune to error in practical matters, in calling people to religion, and in the perception of divine knowledge.<ref>{{harvnb|Ansariyan|2007|p=89}}</ref> [[Shia]]s believe the Fourteen Infallibles are superior to the rest of creation and to the other major [[Prophets in Islam|prophets]].<ref name=\"harvnb|Algar|1990\">{{harvnb|Algar|1990}}</ref>\n\n== Family tree ==\n[[File:Names of imameen.jpg|thumb|right|Calligraphic depiction of fourteen infallibles names.]]\n{{Familytree/start}}\n{{Familytree|boxstyle=background: #DDFFDD| | |MHMAD| | | | |MHMAD=[[Muhammad]]<br/>({{lang|ar|\u0645\u064f\u062d\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0651\u062f}})}}\n{{Familytree|boxstyle=background: #DDFFDD| | | |!| | | | ||}}\n{{Familytree|boxstyle=background: #DDFFDD| | | FTM |y| AL| |FTM=[[Fatimah]]<br/>({{lang|ar|\u0641\u064e\u0627\u0637\u0650\u0645\u064e\u0629}})|AL=[[Ali]]<br/>({{lang|ar|\u0639\u064e\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0651}})}}\n{{Familytree|boxstyle=background: #DDFFDD| | | |,|-|^|-|.| }}\n{{Familytree|boxstyle=background: #DDFFDD| | | HSN | | HSY | | |HSN=[[Hasan ibn Ali|Hasan]]<br/>({{lang|ar|\u0671\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0646}})|HSY=[[Husayn ibn Ali|Husayn]]<br/>({{lang|ar|\u0671\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064f\u0633\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646}})}}\n{{Familytree|boxstyle=background: #DDFFDD| | | | | | | |!||}}\n{{Familytree|boxstyle=background: #DDFFDD| | | | | | | ABH | | |ABH=[[Ali ibn Husayn|Ali Zayn al-Abideen]]<br/>({{lang|ar|\u0639\u064e\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0651 \u0632\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646 \u0671\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u062f\u0650\u064a\u0646}})}}\n{{Familytree|boxstyle=background: #DDFFDD| | | | | | | |!||}}\n{{Familytree|boxstyle=background: #DDFFDD| | | | | | | MBA | | |MBA=[[Muhammad al-Baqir]]<br/>({{lang|ar|\u0645\u064f\u062d\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0651\u062f \u0671\u0644\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0627\u0642\u0650\u0631}})}}\n{{Familytree|